  })), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "But, it has other qualities very close to the same as the vector equilibrium. And those the vector equilibrium has a characteristic of \"twentiness,\" and the prime number five is in it. Whereas in the octahedron it has the prime number six there are six vertexes, and there are four faces and so forth the prime number two is in there, the prime number three is in there. But in vector equilibrium we first come to the prime number five is in there. We find the icosahedron the same prime number five, see? Pending five around each corner and so forth. It is a very fundamentally \"fiveness.\" Now then, that \"fiveness\" is in here as a basic characteristic of the either the vector equilibrium and by the way the vector equilibrium I now write this way \"VE\" because I have to keep saying it all the time, so I use that symbol for it. And so this here is really two times five times frequency to the second power plus two. There is a multiplicative two showing here and there is an additive two, with the prime number five and frequency to the second power. Frequency to the second power is a very intriguing matter, because we have now layers something growing around, absolutely symmetrically, like waves. It's an omnidirectional wave phenomena and every way characterized by the great electromagnetic fundamental wave phenomena omni-directional wavings. Propagation.", mdx("span", {
